---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const structuredData = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Ömer Taha Türkmen',
  description: 'Student writing about geopolitics, economics, and faith.',
  url: new URL('/about', Astro.site).toString(),
};
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="About Ömer Taha Türkmen, a student writing about geopolitics, economics, and faith."
  structuredData={structuredData}
>
  <section class="prose" style="padding: 2rem 0 3rem;">
    <p class="eyebrow">about</p>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      I’m Omer Taha Turkmen, a high school student in Lynnfield, Massachusetts. I
      write about how geopolitics, economics, and faith fit together — not because I
      have figured them out, but because I am trying to.
    </p>

    <p>
      I spent the first fourteen years of my life in Turkey. Moving to the United States
      at fourteen was the kind of change that makes you see everything twice: once from
      where you came from, and once from where you are now. That double view is where
      most of my questions come from.
    </p>

    <p>
      My interest in this world started earlier than I can fully explain. In fifth grade,
      I sat through a Model UN conference in Antalya, and something about it stuck. I kept
      reading history on my own long after any assignment asked me to. When my father
      pointed me toward International Relations, the pieces I had been collecting finally
      had a name.
    </p>

    <p>
      Most of what I write lives at the intersection of politics, religion, and economics:
      how belief shapes power, how a single economic decision quietly reaches ordinary
      people, and how a country’s choices can shape lives for decades. As a Muslim, my
      faith is the ground I stand on. It keeps me from treating statecraft as only a
      contest of power and reminds me to ask where justice and human dignity belong in
      the equation.
    </p>

    <p>
      I’m still a student, and these essays are me working things out in public. I will
      get some of it wrong. But if you care about international law, politics, or simply
      making sense of a world that will not sit still, I’m glad you are here.
    </p>

    <p class="colophon-signature">
      <span class="signature-script">omerwrites</span>
      <span>— Ömer Taha Türkmen</span>
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>
